I"'<h1 id="colors">Colors</h1>

<p>You need to choose a color when creating or editing a preloader.</p>

<p>Available settings:</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Color (with a possibility to use gradient);</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Fill type;</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Fill direction.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr />

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>To add a color, left-click on any area of the color scale (by default, it is painted as a chessboard, there is no color).<br />
<span class="doc_image" id="color" onclick="showModal(this.getAttribute('id'))"><img src="/assets/images/settings/color.gif" alt="color" /></span>
Markers with “anchors” in the lower part will appear. Left-click on them on to select a color.
Color can be removed at any time by clicking on the cross at the top of the marker.</p>
  </li>
  <li>You can choose from 4 fill types:
    <ul>
      <li>Radial
 <button type="button" name="button" onclick="showHide('category_radial')" class="btn btn-purple"> ▼</button><br />
 <span class="category_radial"><img src="/assets/images/settings/radial.png" alt="color" /></span></li>
      <li>Linear
 <button type="button" name="button" onclick="showHide('category_linear')" class="btn btn-purple"> ▼</button><br />
 <span class="category_linear"><img src="/assets/images/settings/linear.png" alt="color" /></span></li>
      <li>Repeating radial
 <button type="button" name="button" onclick="showHide('r_radial')" class="btn btn-purple"> ▼</button><br />
 <span class="r_radial"><img src="/assets/images/settings/repeat_radial.png" alt="color" /></span></li>
      <li>Repeating linear
 <button type="button" name="button" onclick="showHide('r_linear')" class="btn btn-purple"> ▼</button><br />
 <span class="r_linear"><img src="/assets/images/settings/repeat_linear.png" alt="color" /></span></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>You can also choose a direction for each type.
    <ul>
      <li>Radial
